Medication Costs

pre.period <- c(1, 7)
post.period <- c(8, 18)
impact1 <- CausalImpact(arzcost2[,c(2,6,7,8,9,10)], pre.period, post.period, model.args = list(niter = 2000))
impact1

Sensitivity Analysis

For this sensitivity analysis we define an imaginary intervention during the pre-intervention phase.

Medication

pre.period <- c(1, 5)
post.period <- c(6, 7)
impact1_sens <- CausalImpact(arzcost2[-c(8:18),c(2,6,7,8,9,10)], pre.period, post.period, model.args = list(niter = 2000))
impact1_sens
## Posterior inference {CausalImpact}
## 
##                          Average        Cumulative  
## Actual                   343            687         
## Prediction (s.d.)        359 (15)       719 (30)    
## 95% CI                   [329, 390]     [658, 780]  
##                                                     
## Absolute effect (s.d.)   -16 (15)       -32 (30)    
## 95% CI                   [-47, 14]      [-93, 29]   
##                                                     
## Relative effect (s.d.)   -4.5% (4.2%)   -4.5% (4.2%)
## 95% CI                   [-13%, 4%]     [-13%, 4%]  
## 
## Posterior tail-area probability p:   0.14064
## Posterior prob. of a causal effect:  86%
## 
## For more details, type: summary(impact, "report")
plot(impact1_sens)
